metadata.description: Pokemon Trading Card Game Jungle Set - Complete 64 Card Set

cards.name: Clefable

attacks.name: Metronome
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. Metronome copies that attack except for its Energy costs. (You must still do anything else required for that attack.)

attacks.name: Minimize
attacks.text: All damage done to Clefable during your opponent's next turn is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

cards.description: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

cards.name: Electrode

attacks.name: Tackle
attacks.text: Tackle does 10 damage to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Chain Lightning
attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, choose 1 of them and this attack does 10 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

cards.description: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

cards.name: Flareon

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Flamethrower
attacks.text: Discard 1 Fire Energy card attached to Flareon in order to use this attack.

cards.description: When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.

cards.name: Jolteon

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage; if tails, this attack does 10 damage.

attacks.name: Pin Missile
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

cards.description: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000-volt lightning bolts.

cards.name: Kangaskhan

attacks.name: Fetch
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Comet Punch
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

cards.description: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch until it is 3 years old.

cards.name: Mr. Mime

attacks.name: Meditate
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 more damage for each damage counter on the Defending Pokémon.

cards.description: If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.

cards.name: Nidoqueen

attacks.name: Boyfriends
attacks.text: If Nidoking is on your Bench, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage. If there is no Nidoking on your Bench, this attack does 20 damage.

attacks.name: Mega Punch
attacks.text: Mega Punch does 50 damage to the Defending Pokémon.

cards.description: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

cards.name: Pidgeot

attacks.name: Wing Attack
attacks.text: Wing Attack does 20 damage to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hurricane
attacks.text: Unless this attack Knocks Out the Defending Pokémon, return the Defending Pokémon and all cards attached to it to your opponent's hand.

cards.description: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as Magikarp.

cards.name: Pinsir

attacks.name: Irongrip
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Guillotine
attacks.text: Guillotine does 50 damage to the Defending Pokémon.

cards.description: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.

attacks.name: Swords Dance
attacks.text: During your next turn, Scyther's Slash attack's base damage is 60 instead of 30.

attacks.name: Slash
attacks.text: Slash does 30 damage to the Defending Pokémon.

cards.description: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.

cards.name: Snorlax

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

cards.description: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

attacks.name: Water Gun
attacks.text: Does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Vaporeon but not used to pay for this attack's Energy cost.

cards.description: Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.

attacks.text: If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with the Defending Pokémon. (Do the damage before switching the Pokémon.)

attacks.text: Remove a number of damage counters from Butterfree equal to half the damage done to the Defending Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance) (rounded up to the nearest 10). If Butterfree has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.
